“I’ve never seen such a smooth boarding procedure in my entire professional career,” he said.
I was expecting to see teeth scratching and a fight breaking out at the door.
The plane was full, he added, “passengers boarded at lightning speed.”
Frontier also does like Spirit and applies a $2 fee for a coffee, tea, soda or fruit juice.
Frontier said passengers who take a soda or fruit juice can take the unopened box with them, and those who drink coffee can be served for free.
They will be distributing water for free.
US Airways briefly attempted to get paid for drinks in 2008 but came back seven months later after passengers complained and while no other major airline had followed.
