In the third quarter ended September 30, Bombardier’s net profit fell to $147 million, or 8 cents per share, from $172 million, or 9 cents per share, a year earlier.
The adjusted profit per share remained unchanged at 9 cents.
Revenue dropped slightly from $4.2 billion to $4.1 billion.
