George Kerevan: The breakup of Europe gives Scots a choice
Another day, another disturbing history of independence.
This time, we are warned that an independent Scotland would be required to join the European Free Movement Area in order to join the EU.
And now we hear stories of passport control in Berwick and a border of barbed threads along Hadrian’s wall.
While it is true that the Strathclyde newspaper indicated the possible economic consequences of greater freedom of movement with the rest of Europe, this was not in the headlines (and it was to be foreseen).
