French police will arrest Anderlecht supporters who came otherwise than with RSCA cars
French police have decided to set strict rules regarding the match between the Royal Sporting Club of Anderlecht and Paris Saint-Germain scheduled for Tuesday, Marie Verbeke, a spokeswoman for the Brussels-midi police area, said on Friday.
Belgian RSCA supporters who want to go to this Champions League match will have to use the transfer system set up by the RSCA.
“The bus convoy will be escorted by police from a former border post in Rekem to the PSG stadium,” the spokeswoman said.
The process will be the same for the return.
“If other supporters had an intention to travel to Paris by other means, the French police prefecture has made known that measures have been taken to allow for arrests or even guards in sight,” said Marie Verbeke.
